Deutsche Bank shares drop after report of $14 billion fine
Deutsche Bank AG DB, -1.38% shares fell in the extended session Thursday following a report that the Justice Department was proposing the bank pay $14 billion in fines to resolve a probe into mortgage securities. Deutsche Bank shares slipped 6.8% to $13.75 after hours. The figure is preliminary, according to The Wall Street Journal, and has been discussed between the bank and government lawyers in recent days.